commentPreTextItems.html: Heavy rains and thunderstorms in Dubai, we have a delayed start. The umpires will have an inspection at 12:00pm. We are approaching the cut-off time. Good news...play about to start and it will be a 20-over match. Just as the game was about to start, it starts to rain and the game has been called off.

seriesStories.title: Zadran onslaught too much for Ireland
seriesStories.subTitle: Afghanistan v Ireland, Dubai Triangular Series
seriesStories.seoTitle: Najibullah Zadran onslaught too much for Ireland
seriesStories.summary: Afghanistan responded to their heavy defeat against Scotland by inflicting a 71-run loss on Ireland which means the final match on Monday will decide who comes out on top

image.caption: Najibullah Zadran drives
image.longCaption: Najibullah Zadran drives, Afghanistan v Nepal, World T20, Chittagong, March 20, 2014

seriesStories.title: All-round Davey crushes Afghanistan
seriesStories.subTitle: Dubai Triangular Series 2014-15
seriesStories.summary: A six-wicket haul from the fast bowler Josh Davey helped bundle Afghanistan out for 63 and set up Scotland's 150-run win in Abu Dhabi

seriesStories.title: N O'Brien 80* steers Ireland to win
seriesStories.subTitle: Ireland v Scotland, Dubai triangular series
seriesStories.seoTitle: N O'Brien 80* steers Ireland to win
seriesStories.summary: Niall O'Brien's unbeaten 80 anchored Ireland's 217-run chase and led them to a three-wicket win over Scotland, their second victory of the triangular series

image.caption: Niall O'Brien plays one fine to third man
image.longCaption: Niall O'Brien plays one fine to third man, Ireland v Pakistan, 2nd ODI, Dublin, May 26, 2013

seriesStories.title: Ireland survive wobble to win
seriesStories.subTitle: Afghanistan v Ireland, Dubai Triangular Series
seriesStories.summary: Ed Joyce's 51 and a steady 52-run partnership between Andy Balbirnie and Alex Cusack helped Ireland survive a couple of batting wobbles to secure a three-wicket win against Afghanistan in their opening game of the Dubai triangular series

image.caption: Javed Ahmadi celebrates his half-century
image.longCaption: Javed Ahmadi celebrates his half-century, Zimbabwe v Afghanistan, 3rd ODI, Bulawayo, July 22, 2014

seriesStories.title: Javed Ahmadi and Nasir Jamal sink Scotland
seriesStories.subTitle: Afghanistan v Scotland, Dubai Triangular Series
seriesStories.seoTitle: Javed Ahmadi and Nasir Jamal sink Scotland
seriesStories.summary: A strong batting display from Afghanistan's top order, powered by half-centuries from Javed Ahmadi and Nasir Jamal, helped the team to an eight-wicket victory against Scotland in Dubai

image.caption: Nasir Jamal top-scored with 61 for Afghanistan
image.longCaption: Nasir Jamal top-scored with 61 for Afghanistan, Afghanistan v South Africa, Under-19 World Cup 2014, quarter-final, Sharjah, February 23, 2014
